<Layout title="ADC Team details">
  <main id="main">

    <!-- ======= Breadcrumbs ======= -->
    <div class="breadcrumbs d-flex align-items-center" style="background-image: url('assets/img/hero-carousel/hero-carousel-11.jpg');">
      <div class="container position-relative d-flex flex-column align-items-center" data-aos="fade">

        <h2>Team Details</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
          <li>Team Details</li>
        </ol>

      </div>
    </div><!-- End Breadcrumbs -->

    <!-- ======= Blog Details Section ======= -->
    
      <section id="team-2" class="blog">
        <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
  
          <div class="row g-5">
  
            <div class="col-lg-8">
  
              <article class="team-details">     
                <div class="meta-top">
                  <h2>REBECCA RUZIBUKA</h2>
                  <p><h4>Chairperson</h4></p>
                </div><!-- End meta top -->
  
                <div class="content">
                  <p class="align">
                    Rebecca Ruzibuka is a Director of ADC Tanzania Ltd. She has accumulated more than 35 years of experience working in Tanzania and Rwanda in academics and as a Consultant in areas of Business Development Services (BDS). Presently Rebecca is involved in the implementation of the USADF- Rwanda Program as a Program Director of the partner organization -Africa Development Consultant Ltd.
                  </p>  
                  <p class="align">
                    Her other recent accomplishments include Lead Consultant for “Business Planning on behalf of the Post-Harvest and Agribusiness Support Project (PASP), “Develop Business Plans on behalf of NAEB/PRICE Project Beneficiaries for easy access to Financial Services both projects funded by IFAD through Rwanda Ministry of Agriculture, “Cooperative Business Management Capacity Building Training Program for the Rwanda National - Agricultural Export Development Board (NAEB)” funded by IFC. She conducted the Organizational Capacity Assessment and facilitated the 3 Rwanda SMEs funded by the Global Alliance for Improved Nutrition (GAIN) in business modelling and developed a 5 year Business Plan (October 2018 – February 2019). She also provided Technical Assistance to SMEs supported in Rwanda and Tanzania by the  Aceli Africa Inc.
                    Rebecca’s experience in academics include a Lecturer of Business Management and Materials management subjects at the Institute of Development Management (IDM) now Mzumbe University (1991-2001), Head of Entrepreneurship Depart and Senior Lecturer of Business Management subjects.
                    Also, she was a Manager of the University Technology and Business Incubation Facility at Kigali Institute of Science and Technology (KIS) now part of the University of Rwanda.
                  </p>
                  <p class="align">
                    Rebecca is a Certified Performance Technologist (CPT) offered by the International Society for Performance Improvement (ISPI) of USA. She possesses a Master of Business Administration (MBA) from Emporia State University, Kansas, USA, 1996; Advanced Diploma in Business Administration (ADBA) from IDM, Tanzania. She is also a Certified Supplies Professional (CSP) offered by the Tanzania Board of Materials Management. Rebecca was also the Marketing Manager of the Morogoro Leather Goods Company Ltd in Tanzania (1985- 1991).
                  </p> 
                </div><!-- End post content -->             
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-4">     
                   <div class="post-img">
              <img src="assets/img/blog/rebecca.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
            </div>
          </div>  
        </div>
      </section> 
  </main><!-- End #main -->
</Layout>